  - Repeated restarts of the worker with env vars that enable the hook and diagnostics, and subsequent testing sequences. While these are part of the feature validation, in production environments they must be isolated behind feature flags or dedicated test namespaces to avoid leaking test artifacts to tenants or affecting production behavior.
- Sanitization efforts (extractHostname for DATABASE_URL and RABBITMQ_URL) are good, and a quick self-check demonstrated hostnames like postgres and rabbitmq were obtained without credentials. However, any telemetry/diagnostics pipeline involving environment-derived data should be governed by clear data governance and privacy requirements to prevent subtle leakage of internal topology.

